# Cursor Guidelines for Old Reliable

The following rules describe coding conventions and project guidelines.

## General
- Use TypeScript with strict typings across the codebase. Avoid `any` whenever possible.
- Prefer existing libraries over creating custom utilities.
- Never add "example" files unless explicitly requested.
- Keep the codebase free of unused or commented code.

## Next.js
- Use the `app` directory and React Server Components where applicable.
- Use `next/link` and `next/navigation` for routing.
- Configure environment variables via `process.env` with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix for client-side usage.
- Favor dynamic imports with `next/dynamic` when components are heavy or browser-only.

## React
- Use functional components and React hooks. Avoid class components.
- Do not use `React.FC`; type component props explicitly.
- Co-locate component files under `src/components` and keep them small and focused.
- Reuse existing components instead of duplicating functionality.

## Tailwind CSS
- Compose class names using the `cn()` utility from `src/lib/utils` (which combines `clsx` and `tailwind-merge`).
- Use `class-variance-authority` for variant management when creating reusable components.
- Keep global styles minimal; prefer utility classes and components.

